Package: sitch
Title: Checks for Various Computing Environments
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Brian", "Connelly", , "bdc@bconnelly.net", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9948-0379"))
Description: sitch is a collection of lightweight functions that can be
    used to determine the computing environment in which your code is
    running. This includes Continuous Integration (CI) environments,
    containers, different operating systems, and more.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Imports: 
    curl,
    glue,
    lifecycle,
    rlang,
    rstudioapi
Suggests:
    config,
    covr,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    withr
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/testthat/parallel: true
Encoding: UTF-8
